{"lemma":"طَبِيخُ","slug":"طَبِيخُ","root":"ط.ب.خ","root_slug":"ط-ب-خ","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ب-خ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26296","n26302"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AE%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26296","headword_ar":"طَبِيخٌ","root":"Tbx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTobuwxN","text_ar":"مَطْبُوخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cooked;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; but accord. to general usage, it is an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cooked flesh-meat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh-meat cooked with broth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gravy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"what is cooked without broth or gravy not being thus termed: (Msb:) or, as El-Karkhee says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what has broth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gravy, and contains flesh"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"dry fried meat, and the like, not being thus termed: (Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadiyrN","text_ar":"قَدِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signifies either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh-meat cooked in a pot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh-meat cooked in a pot with seeds to season it such as pepper and cumin-seeds and the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qdyr","text_ar":"قدير"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to that which is with seeds to season it, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabiyx","text_ar":"طَبِيخ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which is not seasoned with seeds such as pepper and cumin-seeds and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:) [pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTobixapN","text_ar":"اَطْبِخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and cooked flesh-meat is also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiboxN","text_ar":"طِبْخٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A decoction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense in medical and other books. (See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TubaAxapN","text_ar":"طُبَاخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)] ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sort of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munaS~af","text_ar":"مُنَصَّف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beverage, cooked until half of it has evaporated"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M, A, K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gypsum:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"baked bricks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) These are said to be meant by the last word in the following trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA A^araAda A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"اـِذَا اَرَادَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEabodK suwo'FA jaEala maAlahu fiY AlT~abiyxayoni","text_ar":"بِعَبْدٍ سُوْءًا جَعَلَ مَالَهُ فِى الطَّبِيخَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When God desires evil to befall a man"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a servant"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He makes his property to consist in gypsum and baked bricks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","Mgh","L","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n26302","headword_ar":"طِبِّيخٌ","root":"Tbx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (A, L, K,) written by Aboo-Bekr"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~iyx","text_ar":"طَبِّيخ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"T","text_ar":"ط"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biT~iyxN","text_ar":"بِطِّيخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"melon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or particularly the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water-melon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (L, K:) of the dial. of El-Hijáz, (L,) or of El-Medeeneh. (A.) [Freytag says that, accord. to some, but he does not not name his authority, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large, round melon, rough to the touch, and without a neck, different from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTyx","text_ar":"بطيخ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is a small melon."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["A","L","K"]}]}}